Package frc.robot

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Constants
    The Constants class provides a convenient place for teams to hold robot-wide numerical or boolean constants.
    Main
    Do NOT add any static variables to this class, or any initialization at all.
    Robot
    The VM is configured to automatically run this class, and to call the functions corresponding to each mode, as described in the TimedRobot documentation.
    RobotContainer
    RobotContainer is the place where Subsystems and Commands are declared.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Constants.PID_Constants
    PID(Proportion, Integral, Derivative) Loop Constants: kTurn: Turning the robot from Limelight's X-position(Demo Only) kMaintainDistance: Moves the robot based on calculated distance from Limelight's Y-Position(Demo Only) kShooter: Tuning the speed of the shooter wheels kGyro: Turns based off of angle from Gyro Sensor kDrive: Drives based on encoder values
    Constants.TalonID
    Motor ID numbers and what they correspond to.
